data.description: Charming 1920's Bungalow, nestled in Oakland with a master bedroom and endless potential. This cozy home features 3 bedrooms, 2 bathrooms and original hardwood floors throughout. The open kitchen provides plenty of space for cooking along side a small dining nook with built in shelving. The custom built-ins in the dining area add a unique touch of character and provide additional storage and display space. This home offers the advantage of a central location with easy access to local amenities, schools, parks and transportation options. Outside the home is a small porch and patio with additional storage on the side. The driveway provides tandem parking for 2 cars. With a creative vision and some TLC this home has true potential of a remarkable property. THIS PROPERTY QUALIFIES FOR A BOFA GRANT FOR UP TO $17,500 towards downpayment or closing costs. Please reach out for more information.
